It's gone up a little bit over
time, or something like that.

00:10:46.440 --> 00:10:47.856
SALMAN KHAN: So
it's not too much.

00:10:47.856 --> 00:10:51.020
Maybe $100 or a little bit more
per month, which is nothing.

00:10:51.020 --> 00:10:53.482
I mean, if you're
65 or over, and you

00:10:53.482 --> 00:10:54.940
try to get a private
policy, you're

00:10:54.940 --> 00:10:56.610
probably looking at something
like a thousand dollars

00:10:56.610 --> 00:10:57.060
a month.

00:10:57.060 --> 00:10:57.300
DR. LAURENCE BAKER: Yes.

00:10:57.300 --> 00:10:59.170
So I guess two ways
of thinking about it.

00:10:59.170 --> 00:11:00.503
One, this is heavily subsidized.

