00:12:06.250 --> 00:12:08.394
Kaiser, Blue Cross,
other places.

00:12:08.394 --> 00:12:10.310
Sometimes, they've
contracted with a few PPOs.

00:12:10.310 --> 00:12:12.000
They've tried other
kinds of plans too.

00:12:12.000 --> 00:12:13.580
Mostly it's HMOs.

00:12:13.580 --> 00:12:15.170
So you have a choice then.

00:12:15.170 --> 00:12:21.137
You can join Kaiser, and have
Kaiser be your Medicare plan.

00:12:21.137 --> 00:12:22.470
You can join the Blue Cross one.

00:12:22.470 --> 00:12:23.600
Depending on where
you are, you'll

00:12:23.600 --> 00:12:25.641
have different choices of
different private plans

00:12:25.641 --> 00:12:26.760
that have contracted.

00:12:26.760 --> 00:12:27.830
And you can do that.

00:12:27.830 --> 00:12:30.450
The federal government will
then pay a bunch of your premium

00:12:30.450 --> 00:12:31.290
to them.

00:12:31.290 --> 00:12:31.650
SALMAN KHAN: I see.

00:12:31.650 --> 00:12:34.270
DR. LAURENCE BAKER: So you'll
get covered by the private plan

00:12:34.270 --> 00:12:36.269
with the federal government
covering your costs.

00:12:36.269 --> 00:12:38.490
They might ask you to pay
some additional premium.

00:12:38.490 --> 00:12:40.948
You're going to have to pay
your Part B equivalent already.

00:12:40.948 --> 00:12:42.550
So you've got to
pay that amount.

00:12:42.550 --> 00:12:44.710
But then, you might have
to pay a little bit extra.

00:12:44.710 --> 00:12:47.156
And then, you'll get access
to what services that has.

00:12:47.156 --> 00:12:48.780
And for some people,
